# Node dependencies
# This folder contains all the external libraries your project needs. 
# It's usually very large and can be regenerated at any time by running the npm install command.
# We don't want to store this in our repository.
/node_modules

# Environment variables file
# This file is used to store private information like passwords and API keys. 
# This is critical for security; it should never be committed to Git.
.env

# VS Code specific files
# This folder contains configuration settings for your specific VS Code setup. 
# It's not part of the project itself, so we want to ignore it.
.vscode

# Log files and OS generated files: These are temporary files and are not necessary for the project.
# Log files
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# OS generated files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db